name: sawing and planing, azobe, air dried | residual wood, dry | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10482/documentation

This dataset represents the sawing and planing of one m3 Azobe logs. The debarked Azobe wood logs have been imported to Europe from Central Africa. ;;The sawing and planing process produces panels of which production data are from a sawmill in the Netherlands. The sawmill uses modern equipment and is considered representative for Europe.; ;Natural drying is assumed. It is also assumed that 30% of log input, including sapwood, is generated as co-product that is sold or used for energy recovery outside this process.

Sawing and planing processes starting from debarked Azobe logs at sawmill in Europe.

Includes transportation to sawmill by lorry; sawing and plaining of azobe log in 20 mm sawn timber boards; natural drying is assumed; 30% of log input (including sapwood) is generated as co-product that is sold or is used for energy recovery used outside this process.
category: C:Manufacturing/16:Manufacture of wood and of products of wood and cork, except furniture; manufacture of articles of straw and plaiting materials/161:Sawmilling and planing of wood/1610:Sawmilling and planing of wood

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Wood from Central Africa, sawing in Europe
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Data extrapolated from Meranti window production in the Netherlands. Depending on sawing technology, specific wood density of a particular log and type of sawn timber produced, data may vary
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: see Technology This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography RER. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
